Class CheckingsView

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container
        • javax.swing.JComponent
          • javax.swing.JPanel
            • views.View
              • views.CheckingsView
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class CheckingsView
extends View
    The checkings view of the application. This view is no more no less the 'Checkings history' tab of the application. Its role is exclusively to handle the writing/reading in/of the swing elements and listen for the user's actions. Note : see the checkings controller for the list of the possible actions and their implementations.
    Author:
    Charles MECHERIKI
